fields.name: Pest
fields.description: Unwanted organism, such as insects, rodents, or weeds, that can cause harm or damage.

fields.name: Insect
fields.description: A class of arthropods with three body segments, six legs, and wings in some species.

fields.name: Crawling Insect
fields.description: A type of insect that moves around on its legs and body, such as ants, cockroaches, and bed bugs.

fields.name: Cockroach
fields.description: A type of crawling insect that is flattened, has long antennae and legs, and is known for its ability to adapt to various environments.

fields.name: German Cockroach
fields.description: Small light brown or tan insect, with two black stripes on its back. Often found in kitchens, bathrooms, and other areas with moisture.

fields.name: American Cockroach
fields.description: Large reddish-brown insect, with a yellowish figure-8 pattern on its head. Often found in commercial and residential buildings.

fields.name: Oriental Cockroach
fields.description: Dark brown or black insect, with a shiny appearance. Often found in damp areas, such as basements and sewers.

fields.name: Flying Insect
fields.description: A type of insect that has wings and can fly, such as flies, mosquitoes, and wasps.

fields.name: Mosquito
fields.description: Small flying insect with long legs, a slender body, and elongated mouthparts used to feed on blood. Can transmit diseases to humans and animals.

fields.name: Fruit Fly
fields.description: Small flying insect with a tan or brown body and red eyes. Often found near ripe or decaying fruits and vegetables.

fields.name: Wasp
fields.description: Flying insect with a slender body and two pairs of wings. Can sting multiple times and cause allergic reactions.

fields.name: Bed Bug
fields.description: Small, reddish-brown insects that feed on blood and are often found in homes, hotels, and other areas where people sleep.

fields.name: Rodent
fields.description: A type of mammal characterized by their continuously growing incisors and their ability to gnaw on various materials. They can be pests and pose health risks, as they can transmit diseases and cause damage to property.

fields.name: Mouse
fields.description: A small, light brown or gray rodent with a pointed nose and large ears. They are characterized by their continuously growing incisors and their ability to gnaw on various materials. Often found in homes, restaurants, and other areas with food sources.

fields.name: Rat
fields.description: A larger rodent with a blunt nose and small ears. They are characterized by their continuously growing incisors and their ability to gnaw on various materials. Often found in basements, sewers, and other areas with moisture.

fields.name: House Mouse
fields.description: Small, light brown or gray rodent with a pointed nose and large ears. Often found in homes, restaurants, and other areas with food sources.

fields.name: Norway Rat
fields.description: Large, brown or gray rodent with a blunt nose and small ears. Often found in basements, sewers, and other areas with moisture.

fields.name: Roof Rat
fields.description: Smaller, dark brown or black rodent with a pointed nose and large ears. Often found in attics, trees, and other elevated areas.
